Usage: . shortcut <option>
       source shortcut <option>

Create shortcuts in one's machine to move faster through directories

At least one argument must be given

Options:
	-h --help
		Prints the usage

	-l --list
		Lists available shortcuts

	-s --set	<name>
		Sets a shortcut to your current directory and sets its *name*

	-r --remove	<name>
		Removes the shortcut *name*

	-g --goto	<name> <additional path>
		Go to the shortcut *name*
